headline: A Q3 Deep Dive: Pharma and Materials Demand Drive Growth, Margin Pressures Persist
summary: Life sciences tools company Agilent Technologies (NYSE:A) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 10.1% year on year to $1.74 billion. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($1.83 billion at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 3.4% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.37 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.
